BARUG: Double Dribble: googledrive package

library(tidyverse)
library(googledrive)
drive_auth(reset = TRUE)
Disabling .httr-oauth by renaming to .httr-oauth-SUSPENDED
Removing google token stashed internally in 'googledrive'.
Waiting for authentication in browser...
Press Esc/Ctrl + C to abort
Authentication complete.

For more info on this see:

  • Github tidyverse/googledrive
  • extensive documentation on Managing OAuth Tokens from the package authors. (Thank you, @JennyBryan)
  • my August 2018 BARUG googlesheets presentation. Specifically this part
mydrive <- drive_find()
tr25 <- drive_find(pattern = "Tr", n_max = 25)
tr25

Get more info on drive_find at (http://googledrive.tidyverse.org/) where youll learn to

  • Find files
  • Upload files
  • Share files
  • Publish files
  • Download files

But wait a sec What the heck is a dribble?

tr25 %>% drive_reveal(what = c('mime_type'))

path, trashed, mime_type, permissions, published

But path can be slow

tr25 %>% drive_reveal(what = 'path')
Items so far: 
200 300 400 500 600 700 798

And permissions may be complicated

tr25_perms <- tr25 %>% drive_reveal(what = 'permissions')
tr25_perms

Permissions is a list (like drive_resource). Well take a look at the first file that is shared and look at its permissions

first_shared <- tr25_perms %>%
  filter(shared) %>%
  slice(1)
first_shared
first_perms <- first_shared$permissions_resource
xx <- first_perms[[1]]$permissions
perms <- tibble(role = map_chr(xx, 'role'),
                type = map_chr(xx, 'type'),
                name = map_chr(xx, 'displayName'))
perms

Dribbles are drive tibbles with list-cols

  • Using list-cols in your dataframe RStudio Video Speaker Deck
  • Tutorial - (https://jennybc.github.io/purrr-tutorial/ls13_list-columns.html)

A list is a vector too, its just not atomic

So dribbles can be manipulated using the regular tidyverse tools

# tr25 %>% drive_reveal(what = c('mime_type'))
tr25 %>% mutate(mime_type = map_chr(drive_resource, 'mimeType'))

Which is helpful when drive_reveal doesnt support what we want to promote from our dribble

# tr25 %>% drive_reveal(what = c('mime_type'))
tr25 %>% mutate(created = map_chr(drive_resource, 'createdTime') %>% as.Date())
